HEADWORD: Felo-de-se
<hw>Fe"lo-de-se`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Felos-de-se</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL. <ets>felo</ets>, E.
<ets>felon</ets> + <ets>de</ets> of, concerning + <ets>se</ets>
self.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who deliberately puts an end to
his own existence, or loses his life while engaged in the commission of
an unlawful or malicious act; a suicide.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

